  "prompt": "Is there any way to adjust title and font default settings in Google docs?",
  "response": "Yes, you can adjust title and font settings in Google Docs:\n\nFont Settings:\n1. Select text you want to modify\n2. Use font dropdown menu in toolbar\n3. Change font type, size, color, etc.\n\nDefault Font:\n1. Go to Tools > Preferences\n2. Choose default font, size, and other formatting\n3. Click \"OK\" to save\n\nTitle Formatting:\n1. Click on the title\n2. Use toolbar to change font, size, color\n3. You can create a custom style for titles\n\nPreset Styles:\n1. Click \"Styles\" dropdown in toolbar\n2. Select or modify existing styles\n3. Choose \"Update to match selection\" to save changes\n\nFor consistent formatting across documents:\n1. Create a template document\n2. Go to File > Make a copy\n3. Use this as your default template\n\nThese methods allow you to customize your Google Docs formatting preferences.",
